description: Is predicted to encode a protein with the following domains: Zinc finger, C2H2 type; Zinc finger C2H2-type; and Zinc finger C2H2 superfamily. Is an ortholog of O. volvulus OVOC12012 and OVOC12297.

Is predicted to encode a protein with the following domains: Zinc finger C2H2-type and Zinc finger C2H2 superfamily. Is an ortholog of C. elegans chrX_pilon.g18934 and ham-2. In C. elegans, ham-2 is involved in cell fate determination; cell migration; and regulation of neuron differentiation.

Predicted to enable NAD+ kinase activity. Is an ortholog of C. elegans chrII_pilon.g5321 and sphk-1. In C. elegans, sphk-1 is involved in mitochondrial unfolded protein response; positive regulation of acetylcholine secretion, neurotransmission; and regulation of locomotion.
Predicted to enable metalloendopeptidase activity and zinc ion binding activity. Predicted to be involved in proteolysis. Is an ortholog of C. elegans chrIV_pilon.g12236 and nas-14.

Is predicted to encode a protein with the following domains: Zinc-finger of C2H2 type; Zinc finger, C2H2 type; Zinc finger C2H2-type; and Zinc finger C2H2 superfamily. Is an ortholog of C. elegans chrI_pilon.g1293 and sem-4. In C. elegans, sem-4 is involved in cell differentiation and negative regulation of transcription by RNA polymerase II.

Is predicted to encode a protein with the following domains: C2H2 type zinc-finger (2 copies); Zinc finger C2H2-type; Zinc finger C2H2 superfamily; Zinc finger protein 277; and ZN622/Rei1/Reh1, zinc finger C2H2-type. Is an ortholog of C. elegans chrV_pilon.g15342 and ztf-7.

Is predicted to encode a protein with the following domains: Transmembrane protein family 132; Transmembrane protein 132; and Transmembrane protein family 132, middle domain. Is an ortholog of C. elegans Y71H2AM.10 and chrIII_pilon.g7147.
